==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[prospectus]]'', from ''[[prospicere]], [[prospectum]]'', to look forward, from ''[[pro#Latin|pro]]'', before, forward + ''[[specere]], [[spicere]]'', to look, to see

===Pronunciation===
*(''noun''): 
**(''[[RP]]''): /ˈprɒspɛkt/, /<tt>"prQspEkt</tt>/
**(''US''): präsʹpĕkt, /ˈprɑːspɛkt/, /<tt>"prA:spEkt</tt>/
*(''verb''): prə-spĕktʹ, /prəˈspɛkt/, /<tt>pr@"spEkt</tt>/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛkt|-ɛkt]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[potential]] things that may come to pass, usually favorable.

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

#{{intransitive}} To search, as for [[gold]].

